<!-- Constant Pattern -->
	<section xml:id="ref.patterns.constant">
		<title>Constant Pattern</title>
		<section xml:id="ref.patterns.constant.body">
			<para>
				In Orc pattern matching, a constant pattern is a match only for the same constant value. 
				It is especially useful in clausal and function definitions based on a constant input.  
				For example, we can define the "base case" of a recursive function in a straightforward way. 
			</para>
			<para><emphasis role="strong">EBNF</emphasis>: <emphasis>P ::= C</emphasis></para>
		</section>
		
		 <section xml:id="ref.patterns.constant.examples">
		  <title>Examples</title>

		  <example xml:id="ref.patterns.constant.examples.one"><title>Base Case Definition</title>
<programlisting language="orc"><![CDATA[
{- Use the format function(CONSTANT) = value for later pattern matching on the constant -}

{- Fibonacci numbers -}
def fib(0) = 1
def fib(1) = 1
def fib(n) = if (n < 0) then 0 else fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)
]]></programlisting>
		  </example>
		</section>
		
